void SpinachGUI::IOSpinSystem::ExtractInteractionMatrix3x3 ( String^  line,
String^  InterName,
Atom^  A,
Atom^  B,
double  factor,
bool  read_once,
int  startIndex,
int &  InterID,
int  FieldsNumber,
int  M1Index,
int  M2Index,
int  M3Index,
Unit^  unit,
InteractionKind  IntKind,
ReferenceFrame^  RefFrame,
InteractionsDictionary^ %  InteractionCollection 
) [protected]

Reads three lines, split them to a number of fields which must be equal to FieldsNumber (for each line) and extracts the interaction matrix creatting the interaction and adding to the InteractionCollection. Can used for multiple frames, but the last frame of data is saved.

Parameters:
line String of the first line(of three) that contains the matrix of the interaction.
InterName Name of interaction in order to have it in the exception-error dialogs.
A First atom of the interaction.
B Second atom of the interaction.
factor Multiplying factor for the elements of the matrix.
read_once Flag showing that atom data are read more than once.
startIndex Staring index of this kind of interaction. used when multiple frames.
InterID Interaction ID used when replacing an interaction data, not during adding new interaction.
FieldsNumber Number of fields that supposinlgy this format have for the interactions data. If not , an exception-errror will be thrown.
M1Index Zero-Index number which shows the field of first element of the matrix.
M2Index Zero-Index number which shows the field of second element of the matrix.
M3Index Zero-Index number which shows the field of third element of the matrix.
unit Unit of the imported interaction matrix data.
IntKind Interaction kind of the imported interaction matrix data.
RefFrame Reference frame of the imported interaction matrix data.
InteractionCollection Collection where the data of the interaction will be saved.

Reads a line, split them to a number of fields which must be equal to FieldsNumber and extracts the isotope and coordinates adding to the AtomCollection. Can used for multiple frames, but the last frame of data is saved.

Parameters:
line String wih a line of the file.
Format Name of format in order to have it in the exception-error dialogs.
read_once Flag showing that atom data are read more than once.
AtomID Atom ID used when replacing an atom data, not during adding new atoms.
FieldsNumber Number of fields that supposinlgy this format have for the atoms data. If not , an exception-errror will be thrown.
IsotopeIndex Zero-Index number which shows the field of the name of isotope.
AtomNumberIndex Zero-Index number which shows the field of the atom number of isotope.
MassIndex Zero-Index number which shows the field of the mass of isotope.
XIndex Zero-Index number which shows the field of X coordinate.
YIndex Zero-Index number which shows the field of Y coordinate.
ZIndex Zero-Index number which shows the field of Z coordinate.
factor A multiplying factor for the coordinates.
AtomCollection Collection where the data of the atom will be saved.
